outline_user_prompt_template:
I need a detailed outline for a YouTube sleep history script.

Title: {title}
Target total script length: {target_words} words.

Return ONLY valid JSON (no markdown fences, no explanation) with this exact structure:
{{
  "sections": [
    {{
      "id": "A",
      "title": "THE HOOK",
      "word_target": "40-60",
      "content_notes": "Detailed notes on what to write...",
      "key_details": ["detail 1", "detail 2"]
    }}
  ]
}}

Create these sections in order:
- A: THE HOOK (40-60 words)
- B: EARLY CTA + SLEEP RITUAL (150-200 words)
- C: THE QUESTION BARRAGE (250-350 words)
- D: THE TIME-TRAVEL DROP (100-150 words)
- Then 6-8 numbered body sections (1, 2, 3...) covering the full topic chronologically. Their word_targets should add up to approximately {target_words} minus 1500 words. Each body section should target 2000-3000 words.
- Final section: OUTRO (500-600 words)

For every section, make content_notes EXTREMELY detailed — include specific historical facts, real names, real dates, real events, vivid sensory details, and specific angles to cover. The writer will use these notes as their sole research source, so be thorough and accurate.

For the short intro sections (A, B, C, D) and OUTRO, list 6-10 key_details. For the numbered body sections (which are now much larger at 2000-3000 words), list 15-20 key_details each — specific facts, names, dates, events, anecdotes, and sensory beats — and write content_notes that are 2-3x longer than you normally would, so the writer has enough material to produce the full word target without padding or repetition.
